jojobyte:
``` javascript
var controller = $.superscrollorama(),
    articles = $('.fly-it:not(.has_animation)'); // only adds animations to elements that have not had it added yet.

articles.each(function(){
    addArticleAnimation(this, controller);
});

function addArticleAnimation(self, ctrl) {
    var articleAnim = new TimelineLite();
        articleAnim.add([
            TweenMax.from( $('.subEl', self), 0.25, {
                opacity: 0
            })
        ]);
                // addTween(target, tween, duration, offset, reverse)
        ctrl.addTween($(self), articleAnim, 0, -50, true);
    $(self).addClass('has_animation');
}
```

Thats how we did it for http://www.discoverforever.com/journey/our-aloe/ which uses infinite scroll to keep loading more articles.
. I should mention the reason I closed this, in case anyone else finds this with a similar issue.

It turns out it was working in real IE 8, but in IE 10 Compatibility mode these features weren't working.
